WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.920
about the author. Robert Louis Stevenson was born in Edinburgh, Scotland on the 13th

00:09.920 --> 00:18.880
of November 1850. He was not a strong child and was often ill, but he liked the stories

00:18.880 --> 00:27.880
about adventures and pirates which his father told him. In the late 1860s he went to Edinburgh

00:27.880 --> 00:37.120
University. At first he decided to study engineering because his father was an engineer.

00:37.120 --> 00:43.960
But Stevenson soon understood that he was not happy with his choice and decided to study

00:43.960 --> 00:51.960
law. It was during this time that he became very interested in literature and he began

00:51.960 --> 01:02.560
writing stories. Many of these were published in magazines. In 1876 Stevenson started travelling

01:02.560 --> 01:11.280
through Belgium and France where he met Fanny Osborne. She was American, eleven years older

01:11.280 --> 01:18.000
than himself and a mother of two children. They fell in love immediately but they did

01:18.000 --> 01:24.800
not get married until 1880. After their marriage they went to live in Scotland with

01:24.800 --> 01:35.680
her son Lloyd. One day Stevenson started telling Lloyd a story about pirates. This was

01:35.680 --> 01:43.480
the beginning of one of Stevenson's most famous stories, Treasure Island. This exciting

01:43.520 --> 01:49.720
adventure story about pirates and treasure became very popular with children and adults

01:49.720 --> 01:58.720
all over the world and Stevenson became a famous writer. In 1886 he wrote his most famous

01:58.720 --> 02:07.480
novel, The Strange Case of Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde. This tells the story of a doctor

02:07.480 --> 02:15.320
who drinks a special potion and develops a horrible new personality. His other important

02:15.320 --> 02:29.160
novels include Kidnapped, 1886, The Black Arrow, 1888 and The Master of Balletry, 1889.

02:29.160 --> 02:37.480
In 1888 Stevenson was still ill and he felt that the cold, wet, Scottish weather was not

02:37.480 --> 02:45.000
good for him. So the family decided to travel to the South Pacific. They spent two years

02:45.000 --> 02:54.000
travelling and visited the islands of Hawaii, Tahiti, Samoa and many others. The warm weather

02:54.000 --> 03:01.840
helped Stevenson a lot so the family decided to live in Samoa. Stevenson liked Samoa and

03:01.840 --> 03:09.320
the people very much and they liked him too. He studied the life and customs of these people

03:09.320 --> 03:16.360
and started writing numerous stories set on the islands. Some of these stories were published

03:16.360 --> 03:27.600
in a collection called Island Nights Entertainment's, 1893. Stevenson died in December 1894 in his

03:27.600 --> 03:36.040
home in Samoa. He was only 44 years old. The people of Samoa buried him on top of Mount

03:36.040 --> 03:52.000
There. Chapter 1 The Letter The bell of Mothouse Castle at Tunstall rang loudly one spring afternoon.

03:52.000 --> 03:56.680
The people of the village looked up at the castle.

03:56.680 --> 04:04.960
What's happening? Asked one man. I don't know. Said another. A messenger brought a letter for

04:04.960 --> 04:10.400
Sir Oliver Oates, the priest half an hour ago. It was from Sir Daniel Brackley.

04:10.400 --> 04:21.480
But why is the bell ringing? Asked an old man. Suddenly a handsome young man appeared on his

04:21.480 --> 04:32.200
grey horse. He was about 18 years old and had brown hair and blue eyes. He had a bow and arrow on

04:32.200 --> 04:42.760
his back. His name was Richard Shelton and he was Sir Daniel's ward. Richard Shelton looked at the

04:42.760 --> 04:49.480
people around him and said, There will be a big battle soon. Sir Daniel wants everyone to fight.

04:50.280 --> 05:00.360
Another battle. Cried an angry woman. This is terrible. Our men go and die in battles and their wives

05:00.360 --> 05:08.920
and children are hungry. We pay high taxes to Sir Daniel and we don't have any money for food.

05:08.920 --> 05:17.240
Said a young mother with three small children. Who is Sir Daniel fighting for today? Asked a

05:17.240 --> 05:26.600
tall man. Lancaster or York? I'm sorry. I don't know. Said Richard and his face became red.

05:28.360 --> 05:37.160
Sir Daniel Brackley was not a loyal man and the people did not like him. He seems to always

05:37.160 --> 05:44.680
change his mind. Sometimes he fought for Lancaster and sometimes he fought for York.

05:45.560 --> 05:56.200
A big man on a black horse appeared. It was Bennett Hatch, Sir Daniel's best friend. He was about 40

05:56.200 --> 06:05.400
and had dark hair and an unfriendly face. All of the men in the village must go to Mote House Castle

06:05.400 --> 06:13.880
and get ready for the battle. Hatch cried. Then Hatch looked at Richard and said, Let's go to

06:14.600 --> 06:19.320
Nick Appleyard's house. When they arrived, Hatch said.

06:20.280 --> 06:26.120
Nick Appleyard, you must go and defend Mote House Castle because Sir Daniel is going to

06:26.120 --> 06:35.640
quickly to fight. While the two men were talking, a black arrow suddenly hit Nick Appleyard in the

06:35.720 --> 06:44.200
back and killed him. Oh no! cried Richard. Appleyard is dead. Someone in the forest shot

06:44.200 --> 06:51.000
this black arrow. Look! There's a message on the arrow. Said Hatch. What does he say, Richard?

06:52.600 --> 07:01.800
Richard took the arrow and read for Appleyard from John to make things right. What a strange

07:01.800 --> 07:10.600
message. It's dangerous here. Let's go to the church. Said Hatch. There were about 20 men on

07:10.600 --> 07:18.360
their horses outside the church. They were ready to fight. Sir Daniel will be pleased with these

07:18.360 --> 07:27.080
brave men. Said Hatch. Look at the church door. Said Richard. There's a letter on it. A letter on

07:27.080 --> 07:34.760
the church door. Said Sir Oliver. Surprised. He was the priest of the village and Sir Daniel's

07:34.760 --> 07:44.840
good friend. Young Richard, please read it. Richard took the letter off the door and read it aloud.

07:45.560 --> 07:54.600
I have four black arrows. The first arrow killed Appleyard. The next one will kill Bennett Hatch

07:54.680 --> 08:04.200
because he burnt Greenstone House. Another arrow is for Sir Oliver Oates because he killed Sir Harry

08:04.200 --> 08:16.520
Shelton. Sir Daniel will get the fourth arrow from John of the Greenwood and his men. P.S. Remember

08:16.520 --> 08:25.960
we have other arrows for your men. We live in a terrible world. I'm a good man. I did not kill

08:25.960 --> 08:35.240
Sir Harry Shelton. Cried Sir Oliver Oates. We know you're a good honest man Sir Oliver. Said Hatch.

08:36.120 --> 08:43.000
Then he whispered something in Sir Oliver's ear and looked at Richard. Sir Harry Shelton was

08:43.080 --> 08:52.120
Richard's father. Richard saw this, but he said nothing. I must write a letter to Sir Daniel

08:52.760 --> 08:59.720
and tell him what happened, said Sir Oliver. When the letter was ready, he said,

09:00.840 --> 09:08.040
Richard, take this important letter to Sir Daniel immediately. Be careful on the road

09:08.040 --> 09:14.760
because it can be very dangerous. Richard took the letter and went to get his horse.

09:16.680 --> 09:25.800
Hatch followed him. Richard, he said quietly, you're a brave, honest young man. Listen to me.

09:26.600 --> 09:35.480
Be careful of Sir Daniel. Don't trust him and don't trust Sir Oliver. They're dangerous men.

09:36.440 --> 09:47.400
Richard was surprised and started thinking. Thank you, my friend, he said. Then he got on his grey horse and galloped away.

09:51.960 --> 10:02.920
Chapter 2 John Matcham. Sir Daniel Brackley sat next to the fire at the sign of the sun in in

10:03.080 --> 10:11.720
Keckley. He was a tall man of about forty. He was born and had a big nose and black eyes.

10:12.920 --> 10:19.080
He collected taxes all day and now he was thinking about how he could make more money.

10:20.120 --> 10:28.760
Sir Daniel was a very greedy man and did many bad things. A thin young boy was sitting near the

10:28.760 --> 10:38.840
door of the inn. He was very sad. Come here, John. Said Sir Daniel. The young boy was about thirteen

10:39.400 --> 10:46.840
and had blonde hair and blue eyes. He was wearing dirty old clothes and a big brown hat.

10:48.600 --> 10:55.880
Sir Daniel looked at him and laughed. You make me laugh, John.

10:56.680 --> 11:05.000
Don't laugh at me. Said John angrily. I don't like it. Oh, let me laugh. Said Sir Daniel.

11:05.000 --> 11:13.240
I'll plan a good marriage for you. You'll see. And I'll make a lot of money with this marriage.

11:13.880 --> 11:22.040
Thought Sir Daniel. Lord Shorby will pay me well. The young boy went to sit down again.

11:22.840 --> 11:33.640
Some time later, Richard came into the inn. Richard, my brave boy. Said Sir Daniel. Sit down and eat.

11:33.640 --> 11:41.240
You're probably hungry and thirsty. Here's an important letter from Sir Oliver, said Richard,

11:41.240 --> 11:50.680
giving him the letter. Sir Daniel read it and he was worried. Richard, the letter on the church door

11:51.080 --> 11:57.000
is alive. Said Sir Daniel. Sir Oliver did not kill your poor father.

11:57.720 --> 12:04.600
Ellis Duckworth killed your father, but he escaped and we never found him.

12:04.600 --> 12:11.000
Did this happen at Motow's castle? Asked Richard, looking into Sir Daniel's eyes.

12:11.720 --> 12:15.560
It happened between Motow's and Hollywood.

12:15.640 --> 12:22.920
Answered Sir Daniel. But now, sit down and eat. I must answer Sir Oliver's letter

12:22.920 --> 12:25.960
and then you can take it back to him in Tunstall.

12:27.240 --> 12:31.800
While Richard was eating, he heard a soft voice near his ear.

12:32.680 --> 12:37.000
Please don't turn around, but tell me the way to Hollywood.

12:37.000 --> 12:44.840
Take the road by the old church. Richard whispered. He did not turn around,

12:45.480 --> 12:52.680
but he saw the boy leave the inn quietly. Take this message to Tunstall immediately.

12:53.480 --> 12:58.280
Said Sir Daniel to Richard. Then he looked around in and said,

12:58.760 --> 13:05.960
Where is that girl? That boy, John. He left the inn about an hour ago.

13:05.960 --> 13:08.760
Said Richard. I must find him.

13:08.760 --> 13:16.520
Cried Sir Daniel. He turned to one of his men and said, James, take six men and go and find that boy.

13:17.640 --> 13:24.600
Richard left the inn with the message. He rode his horse all night and early the next morning,

13:24.600 --> 13:32.280
he was near a marsh. In the marsh, he saw a young boy on his horse, but the horse was not moving.

13:33.320 --> 13:38.200
You're the boy from the inn, said Richard. I saw you last night.

13:39.000 --> 13:46.600
Yes, I am. He said. I'm lost and my horse hurt his leg in the marsh. Now he can't move.

13:47.480 --> 13:54.520
The poor horse, said Richard. I'm sorry, but I must kill it. Please get off.

13:55.720 --> 13:59.000
When the boy got off, he killed the horse.

14:00.360 --> 14:03.720
Can you help me go to Hollywood, Master Shelton?

14:03.720 --> 14:09.160
As the boy. Yes, I can, said Richard, but who are you?

14:09.960 --> 14:16.440
Call me John Matcham. Said the boy. Why do you want to go to Hollywood, John?

14:16.440 --> 14:22.120
Asked Richard. There's a kind fryer at Hollywood and he'll protect me.

14:22.120 --> 14:30.280
Said John. Protect you? Asked Richard. Yes, he'll protect me from Sir Daniel Brackley.

14:30.280 --> 14:38.520
Said the boy. He's a very bad man. He took me from my home and gave me these dirty clothes to wear.

14:39.720 --> 14:43.880
But I know, said Daniel, said Richard. He's not an evil man.

14:44.600 --> 14:51.320
He's evil and greedy. Believe me. Said the boy. One day you'll understand why.

14:52.600 --> 14:59.080
He was silent for a moment and then said, I heard that you are going to get married soon.

15:00.040 --> 15:07.880
What? Said Richard laughing. And who am I going to marry? Joanna Sedley. Said the boy.

15:07.880 --> 15:14.760
Said Daniel planned a marriage. Oh, said Richard and his face became red.

15:15.720 --> 15:23.240
But I don't know her. Suddenly they heard a noise and saw Sir Daniel's seven men on the hill.

15:24.040 --> 15:27.640
Sir Daniel's men. Cried the boy. They're looking for me.

15:28.280 --> 15:34.360
Don't worry. I'll take you to Hollywood. I promise, said Richard. Get on my horse quickly.

15:35.160 --> 15:41.480
John smiled at his new friend and together they galloped into the dark forest.

15:45.320 --> 15:54.120
The Wars of the Roses. There was civil war in England from 1455 to 1485.

15:55.640 --> 16:00.520
This was because of an argument between the families of York and Lancaster.

16:01.320 --> 16:09.000
Each noble family at this time had a picture of an object which they used as a special symbol of their family.

16:09.960 --> 16:19.960
The Lancastrians had a red rose and the Yorkists had a white rose. This gave the name to the Wars of the Roses.

16:21.160 --> 16:27.000
Both the Yorkists and the Lancastrians were descendants of King Edward III,

16:27.960 --> 16:34.120
1327 to 77, and both wanted to be King of England.

16:35.640 --> 16:42.280
In 1455, the King of England was Henry VI, a member of the Lancaster family.

16:43.480 --> 16:49.880
But the leader of the York family, John, Duke of York, also wanted to be King.

16:50.120 --> 16:57.560
The first battle was in 1455 at St. Albans, just north of London.

16:57.560 --> 17:03.240
The Yorkists won, but Henry VI was still King.

17:03.240 --> 17:14.360
Three years passed before the next battle, but between 1459 and 1461, there were eight more battles.

17:14.360 --> 17:24.360
The Yorkists won five of these, and finally, in 1461, there was a Yorkist King for the first time.

17:24.360 --> 17:32.360
Edward IV, 1461 to 70, 1471 to 83.

17:34.360 --> 17:42.200
After Edward IV's death in 1483, the heir to the throne was the eldest son, Edward V.

17:43.080 --> 17:45.240
But he was still a child at this time.

17:46.760 --> 17:53.080
Edward IV's brother, the Duke of Gloucester, was the guardian of both the boy and his younger

17:53.080 --> 18:01.640
brother. The Duke also wanted to be King, so he decided to put the boys in prison in the tower of

18:01.640 --> 18:09.400
London. People believed that they were killed soon after their arrival, and the Duke became

18:09.400 --> 18:16.440
King Richard III. There were seventeen battles during the Thirty Years of War.

18:17.400 --> 18:22.840
These happened all over England, in the north, south, east and west.

18:24.680 --> 18:32.360
On the 22nd of August, 1485, Henry Tudor, a descendant of the House of Lancaster,

18:32.360 --> 18:38.600
won the final battle. Richard III, the last York king, was killed.

18:39.880 --> 18:47.800
Henry Tudor then became King Henry VII. A year later, he married Elizabeth of York,

18:48.360 --> 18:51.960
and the Lancaster and York families would join together.

18:53.240 --> 19:01.240
To show this, the white rose of York and the red rose of Lancaster became one red and white rose.

19:02.440 --> 19:09.080
This was called the Tudor rose, as was the symbol of the Tudors, a new line of English

19:09.080 --> 19:10.120
kings and queens.

19:14.520 --> 19:15.720
Listening activity.

19:18.200 --> 19:21.160
Lawless? Isn't that food ready yet?

19:22.120 --> 19:26.280
Here you are, Ellis. Freshly cooked eggs for the first time in a month.

19:27.640 --> 19:31.640
Well done, Lawless. Where did you get the eggs from?

19:32.200 --> 19:38.520
From a farmhouse near Kettley. Don't worry, Ellis. The band of the Black Arrow has many friends.

19:39.160 --> 19:41.240
We will not be hungry.

19:41.240 --> 19:44.600
You're right, Lawless. We have many loyal friends.

19:45.240 --> 19:49.800
There are many people that hate Sir Daniel Brackley and want to help the band.

19:50.680 --> 19:53.080
They know Brackley is a cruel man.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.280
Just look what he did to your house, Ellis.

19:57.240 --> 20:02.680
Yes, my dear home, burnt down by Bennett Hatch.

20:03.720 --> 20:06.120
Well, he will pay for it.

20:07.000 --> 20:10.840
Listen, Ellis. Someone's coming through the forest.

20:10.840 --> 20:13.800
I think it must be Daniel Brackley's men.

20:14.600 --> 20:18.360
Quick, everyone, hide and get ready to attack.

20:22.520 --> 20:23.400
Chapter 3.

20:24.440 --> 20:26.360
Mote House Castle.

20:28.600 --> 20:33.000
Richard and John rode through the dark forest of Tunstall,

20:33.800 --> 20:36.280
where the tall trees moved in the wind.

20:37.480 --> 20:40.920
They stopped when they found a big, burnt house.

20:42.280 --> 20:45.240
This house looks like Grimstone, said Richard.

20:45.880 --> 20:46.920
Grimstone?

20:46.920 --> 20:47.800
Asked John.

20:47.800 --> 20:48.520
What's that?

20:49.320 --> 20:54.280
It was Ellis Duckworth's house until Bennett Hatch burnt it down five years ago.

20:55.160 --> 20:57.880
It was a very beautiful house before the fire.

20:58.840 --> 21:03.160
Behind the house, they saw some men sitting around a fire.

21:04.120 --> 21:09.000
They were wearing old, dark clothes, and each man had a bow and arrow.

21:09.880 --> 21:13.880
They were eating and talking like old friends, and some were laughing.

21:15.400 --> 21:18.600
Suddenly, a man up a tall tree cried,

21:18.600 --> 21:21.320
I see seven of Sir Daniel's men coming here.

21:22.040 --> 21:23.240
Is Sir Daniel with them?

21:23.800 --> 21:24.920
Asked a handsome man.

21:25.400 --> 21:27.560
No, I can't see him.

21:27.560 --> 21:29.320
An said the man on the tall tree.

21:30.040 --> 21:31.400
Let's attack them.

21:31.400 --> 21:33.080
Cried the handsome man.

21:33.080 --> 21:34.840
Go to your places quickly.

21:36.040 --> 21:41.080
I must go and tell Sir Daniel's men about the attack, said Richard to John.

21:41.080 --> 21:41.800
But why?

21:42.600 --> 21:44.600
Asked John, surprised.

21:44.600 --> 21:46.120
They're looking for me.

21:46.120 --> 21:48.680
You promised to take me to Holywood.

21:48.680 --> 21:49.960
You can't leave me now.

21:50.760 --> 21:53.320
You're right, John, said Richard.

21:53.320 --> 21:54.760
I'll take you to Holywood.

21:56.120 --> 21:57.800
Richard remembered his promise.

21:58.920 --> 22:03.320
The man in the forest took their bows and arrows and ran to their places.

22:04.280 --> 22:06.360
They started attacking Sir Daniel's men.

22:08.040 --> 22:13.800
When the attack was over, one of the men in the forest saw Richard and wanted to kill him.

22:14.760 --> 22:15.560
No, don't!

22:16.200 --> 22:17.400
Cried the handsome man.

22:18.280 --> 22:23.160
It was Ellis stuck with the leader of the band of the Black Arrow.

22:23.960 --> 22:25.560
This boy is Harry's son.

22:26.200 --> 22:27.480
We mustn't hurt him.

22:28.440 --> 22:30.120
Bring him to me immediately.

22:30.920 --> 22:32.280
I want to talk to him.

22:33.160 --> 22:35.000
Richard heard him and said,

22:35.000 --> 22:37.480
Oh no, let's run away from here, John.

22:37.480 --> 22:37.960
Quickly!

22:39.160 --> 22:43.480
The two boys ran to the top of a hill and two men followed them.

22:44.440 --> 22:47.240
John was tired, but he continued running.

22:48.280 --> 22:52.120
They soon reached another forest, and Richard said,

22:52.120 --> 22:53.880
No one is following us now.

22:53.880 --> 22:54.600
We're safe.

22:56.120 --> 22:59.800
I can't walk or run anymore, said John.

22:59.800 --> 23:01.160
I'm very tired.

23:02.120 --> 23:03.080
Tired?

23:03.080 --> 23:04.120
Said Richard.

23:04.120 --> 23:05.800
What kind of a boy are you?

23:07.000 --> 23:09.880
John looked at him and started crying.

23:10.840 --> 23:13.080
Oh, please don't cry.

23:13.160 --> 23:14.760
Said Richard, smiling.

23:14.760 --> 23:16.600
Look, there's a river.

23:16.600 --> 23:18.520
Let's go and drink some cold water.

23:20.200 --> 23:24.280
Later, when it was dark, they fell asleep under a tree.

23:26.360 --> 23:29.160
The next morning, they woke up and were hungry,

23:30.120 --> 23:31.560
but they had nothing to eat.

23:33.160 --> 23:35.880
Suddenly, they heard a noise coming from the forest.

23:36.920 --> 23:39.000
They saw a fryer walking towards them.

23:40.280 --> 23:42.280
His head was covered with a big hood.

23:43.480 --> 23:46.280
He stopped near them and took off his hood.

23:47.640 --> 23:48.920
Sir Daniel!

23:48.920 --> 23:49.960
Cried Richard.

23:49.960 --> 23:51.720
This is a surprise.

23:51.720 --> 23:53.480
What are you doing here?

23:53.480 --> 23:55.560
And why are you dressed like a fryer?

23:56.280 --> 23:57.240
Richard.

23:57.240 --> 23:58.600
Said Sir Daniel.

23:58.600 --> 24:00.840
We lost the battle against York.

24:01.720 --> 24:05.640
It was a terrible battle, and most of my men were killed.

24:06.600 --> 24:09.880
I am wearing fryers' clothes, so I can escape.

24:10.840 --> 24:13.800
Now I'm going home to Mote House Castle.

24:15.080 --> 24:18.040
Sir Daniel gave them both some bread and cheese.

24:19.000 --> 24:22.600
Richard and John ate quickly, because they were very hungry.

24:23.400 --> 24:26.840
I'm surprised to see you two boys together.

24:26.840 --> 24:28.120
Said Sir Daniel.

24:28.120 --> 24:30.200
But now you're both coming with me.

24:31.000 --> 24:32.280
You understand?

24:32.280 --> 24:33.880
Very well, Sir Daniel.

24:33.880 --> 24:35.080
Said Richard.

24:35.080 --> 24:35.800
Yes, sir.

24:36.600 --> 24:37.880
Said John quietly.

24:38.760 --> 24:43.480
Richard and John followed Sir Daniel, and they soon arrived at the castle.

24:44.040 --> 24:46.600
Before going in, John said,

24:46.600 --> 24:50.040
Well, Richard, now we must say goodbye.

24:50.040 --> 24:52.680
But why, said Richard.

24:52.680 --> 24:55.480
We're both going to Mote House Castle.

24:55.480 --> 24:59.160
We're good friends, and we can see each other all the time.

24:59.160 --> 25:01.400
You won't see me anymore.

25:01.400 --> 25:03.160
Said John sadly.

25:03.160 --> 25:05.640
And I can't explain why.

25:05.720 --> 25:08.040
I must do what Sir Daniel says.

25:08.040 --> 25:12.440
But remember, Richard, be careful of Sir Daniel.

25:13.960 --> 25:18.040
Richard did not like this mystery, and wanted to know more.

25:18.040 --> 25:22.360
Goodbye, my young friend, said Richard sadly.

25:24.360 --> 25:32.440
Mote House Castle was a stone castle, with a drawbridge, a mote, and four tall towers.

25:33.080 --> 25:38.760
There were now only 22 men in the castle, because a lot of them were killed during

25:38.760 --> 25:40.760
the last battle against York.

25:42.200 --> 25:48.440
These men were afraid of the band of the Black Arrow, because the band lived in the forest near the castle.

25:49.640 --> 25:53.480
Richard went to his bedroom and closed the door.

25:53.480 --> 25:57.320
It was a big, cold room near the top of the castle.

25:57.320 --> 26:00.280
He did not have many things inside.

26:00.280 --> 26:04.360
Just a large bed, a table, and chair.

26:04.360 --> 26:10.120
Richard liked the room, because it was somewhere he could stay on his own and think.

26:10.120 --> 26:16.040
Now he went to sit on the bed, so he could think about all the recent events.

26:16.040 --> 26:19.480
What's happening at Mote House Castle?

26:19.480 --> 26:20.840
He thought.

26:20.840 --> 26:24.440
Why can't I see my friend John Matchum anymore?

26:24.440 --> 26:28.120
Why is everyone telling me to be careful of Sir Daniel?

26:28.200 --> 26:30.200
Who is Joanna saidly?

26:30.200 --> 26:33.160
How can I marry her if I don't know her?

26:33.160 --> 26:39.640
Richard was very confused, and looked out of the small window in his room.

26:39.640 --> 26:46.200
He could see the big forest, and he started thinking about the letter from John of the Greenwood.

26:46.200 --> 26:50.680
The letter says, Sir Oliver killed my father, he thought.

26:50.680 --> 26:53.880
But Sir Daniel says, the letter is not true.

26:53.880 --> 26:55.640
He says, the letter is not true.

26:55.800 --> 26:58.760
He says, Ellis Duckworth killed him.

26:58.760 --> 27:01.960
Did Ellis Duckworth really kill him?

27:01.960 --> 27:07.000
I don't believe Sir Daniel, because I think he's hiding something from me.

27:07.000 --> 27:08.600
But what?

27:08.600 --> 27:13.000
I want to know the truth, and must know the truth.

27:13.000 --> 27:17.800
And only Sir Daniel can answer my questions.

27:17.800 --> 27:21.480
Chapter 4

27:22.360 --> 27:24.840
Chapter 4

27:24.840 --> 27:28.440
Joanna saidly.

27:28.440 --> 27:32.680
Someone knocked on Richard's door.

27:32.680 --> 27:34.920
It was Bennett Hatch.

27:34.920 --> 27:36.360
Good afternoon, Richard.

27:36.360 --> 27:39.800
He said, Sir Daniel wants to see you immediately.

27:39.800 --> 27:41.400
Good, said Richard.

27:41.400 --> 27:43.400
I want to see him too.

27:43.400 --> 27:45.720
I have a lot of things to ask him.

27:45.720 --> 27:48.760
There are too many mysteries at Mote House Castle.

27:48.840 --> 27:50.760
Too many things I don't understand.

27:51.560 --> 27:53.640
Sir Daniel is not telling me the truth.

27:54.360 --> 27:55.880
Richard, said Hatch.

27:56.600 --> 27:57.720
Please be careful.

27:58.520 --> 28:01.480
Don't ask Sir Daniel certain questions.

28:02.680 --> 28:04.120
What do you mean, Hatch?

28:04.120 --> 28:04.920
Asked Richard.

28:05.800 --> 28:10.200
Well, you know, certain questions about...

28:10.920 --> 28:12.920
I want answers to my questions.

28:13.640 --> 28:14.760
Said Richard angrily.

28:15.480 --> 28:17.400
And he went to Sir Daniel's room.

28:18.920 --> 28:20.040
Sir Oliver was there.

28:20.920 --> 28:22.840
He was sitting in a corner of the room,

28:23.480 --> 28:24.840
and his face was white.

28:26.280 --> 28:27.880
Come in, Richard.

28:27.880 --> 28:28.760
Said Sir Daniel.

28:29.320 --> 28:30.280
Please sit down.

28:31.320 --> 28:33.320
You look worried, my boy.

28:34.120 --> 28:38.120
Are you still thinking about that letter on the church door?

28:38.840 --> 28:41.320
Yes, and I want some answers.

28:41.320 --> 28:42.120
Said Richard.

28:42.120 --> 28:44.840
My father was killed when I was a little boy.

28:44.840 --> 28:47.960
People say that you and Sir Oliver killed him.

28:48.040 --> 28:49.160
I want to know the truth.

28:51.640 --> 28:57.160
Oh, Richard, do you really think I killed your father?

28:57.160 --> 28:58.840
Said Sir Daniel, smiling.

28:59.560 --> 29:01.560
Your father was my friend.

29:02.600 --> 29:06.760
When he died, I looked after you all these years

29:06.760 --> 29:08.440
and taught you many things.

29:09.240 --> 29:11.240
And poor Sir Oliver.

29:12.600 --> 29:16.840
He's a priest, a kind, honest man.

29:16.840 --> 29:20.280
Said Daniel, for many years you used my family's money

29:20.280 --> 29:22.040
because I live with you.

29:22.040 --> 29:23.480
Said Richard angrily.

29:23.480 --> 29:26.920
And you'll soon plan my marriage and get a lot of money for it.

29:26.920 --> 29:29.960
How can you say these terrible things?

29:29.960 --> 29:31.320
Cried Sir Daniel.

29:31.320 --> 29:33.640
You're making me very angry.

29:35.160 --> 29:36.760
But you're still a boy.

29:36.760 --> 29:39.080
We'll talk about this when you're a man.

29:40.040 --> 29:43.560
Remember, I did not kill your father.

29:44.600 --> 29:45.320
I promise.

29:46.120 --> 29:48.360
When Sir Oliver heard the words,

29:48.360 --> 29:51.720
I promise, he jumped in his chair.

29:53.000 --> 29:55.480
Richard saw this and understood a lot.

29:57.480 --> 30:00.120
After he left the room, said Daniel said,

30:00.920 --> 30:03.720
The boy asks too many questions.

30:04.280 --> 30:06.520
He knows too many things.

30:08.280 --> 30:11.000
Put him in the room above the church.

30:11.960 --> 30:14.280
The room above the church?

30:14.280 --> 30:16.440
Asked Sir Oliver quietly.

30:16.440 --> 30:18.360
Yes, you heard me.

30:18.360 --> 30:19.640
Said Sir Daniel.

30:21.160 --> 30:25.400
Richard went to his room and remembered Hatcher's words.

30:26.600 --> 30:30.200
Don't trust Sir Daniel or Sir Oliver.

30:31.080 --> 30:36.040
In the evening, one of Sir Daniel's men came to his room and said,

30:36.040 --> 30:38.040
Follow me, Master Shelton.

30:38.040 --> 30:40.040
You'll sleep in another room.

30:40.040 --> 30:41.960
You'll sleep in another room tonight.

30:41.960 --> 30:43.320
In another room?

30:43.320 --> 30:44.600
Asked Richard.

30:44.600 --> 30:48.040
Yes, in the room above the church.

30:48.040 --> 30:48.920
I said the man.

30:49.560 --> 30:50.840
It's nice and big.

30:52.360 --> 30:53.800
But it's full of ghosts.

30:55.080 --> 30:56.760
Full of ghosts.

30:56.760 --> 30:57.720
Thought Richard.

30:57.720 --> 30:58.600
What does he mean?

31:00.520 --> 31:04.680
Richard sat on the big bed in the new room and he was worried.

31:05.880 --> 31:09.320
He did not know that many men were killed in that room.

31:10.280 --> 31:13.800
I must leave this castle immediately, he thought.

31:13.800 --> 31:15.240
Something bad is happening.

31:17.080 --> 31:19.160
Suddenly, someone knocked on the door.

31:21.400 --> 31:22.680
It was John Matcham.

31:23.800 --> 31:27.480
John, I'm happy to see you, said Richard.

31:27.480 --> 31:28.760
Oh, Richard.

31:28.760 --> 31:29.880
Listen to me.

31:29.880 --> 31:30.840
Said John.

31:30.840 --> 31:33.400
I heard Sir Daniel's men talking.

31:33.400 --> 31:34.520
They want to kill you.

31:35.160 --> 31:36.760
I want to help you escape.

31:37.240 --> 31:39.880
I think there's a secret way out of this room.

31:41.000 --> 31:45.880
They started looking for it and found a small trap door under a table.

31:46.440 --> 31:48.200
This is the secret way out.

31:48.760 --> 31:50.280
Said John excitedly.

31:50.280 --> 31:51.640
We can escape together.

31:52.760 --> 31:54.840
Then they heard Sir Daniel's voice.

31:55.560 --> 31:56.120
Joanna!

31:56.840 --> 31:57.320
Joanna!

31:57.880 --> 31:58.600
Where are you?

31:59.640 --> 32:00.760
Who is Joanna?

32:01.320 --> 32:02.040
Asked Richard.

32:03.560 --> 32:05.480
John looked at Richard and said,

32:06.440 --> 32:07.720
I am Joanna.

32:09.240 --> 32:09.560
You?

32:10.520 --> 32:12.440
Said Richard, surprised.

32:12.440 --> 32:14.200
Then you're not a boy.

32:14.200 --> 32:14.920
You're a girl.

32:15.960 --> 32:17.400
You're Joanna, saidly.

32:18.280 --> 32:20.760
Yes, I'm Joanna, saidly.

32:21.960 --> 32:26.920
She took off her big hat and Richard could see her long blonde hair.

32:28.120 --> 32:29.240
She was very pretty.

32:30.600 --> 32:31.880
You're a brave girl.

32:32.520 --> 32:35.960
Said Richard's smiling, and you're beautiful too.

32:37.320 --> 32:39.400
They could hear Sir Daniel's voice again.

32:40.040 --> 32:40.680
Joanna!

32:41.560 --> 32:42.440
Where are you?

32:43.080 --> 32:45.000
We must escape immediately.

32:45.560 --> 32:46.200
Said Joanna.

32:47.560 --> 32:51.880
They opened the trap door and went down the long secret corridor.

32:52.840 --> 32:56.040
They came to a big door, but it was locked.

32:56.760 --> 32:57.960
What can we do now?

32:58.520 --> 32:59.320
Ask Joanna.

32:59.960 --> 33:02.440
I don't know, said Richard.

33:02.440 --> 33:05.800
Perhaps someone will open this door because we're near the church.

33:06.760 --> 33:07.720
Let's wait here.

33:09.000 --> 33:11.000
They sat down on the stone floor.

33:12.360 --> 33:15.560
Are you Sir Daniel's ward too, asked Richard?

33:16.520 --> 33:19.240
Yes, my mother and father are dead,

33:19.800 --> 33:21.320
and my family was rich.

33:22.360 --> 33:25.000
At first Lord Foxham looked after me.

33:25.560 --> 33:26.680
He was a good man.

33:27.640 --> 33:29.160
Then Sir Daniel took me.

33:30.040 --> 33:33.320
After some time, Lord Foxham took me back.

33:34.360 --> 33:36.440
He wanted me to marry Lord Hamley.

33:37.480 --> 33:41.320
When Sir Daniel heard this, he decided to kidnap me.

33:42.280 --> 33:44.680
He gave me these boys clothes and said,

33:45.240 --> 33:47.320
You will marry Richard Shelton.

33:48.360 --> 33:51.480
Every marriage brings Sir Daniel a lot of money.

33:52.760 --> 33:55.720
I'm happy I met you, Joanna, said Richard.

33:56.440 --> 33:58.440
I am too, she said.

33:59.880 --> 34:02.920
Suddenly they realized someone was behind them.

34:04.120 --> 34:05.320
It was Bennett Hatch.

34:06.200 --> 34:08.600
Hatch, what are you doing here?

34:08.600 --> 34:10.760
Asked Richard, surprised.

34:10.760 --> 34:12.280
I'm looking for you, Richard.

34:12.840 --> 34:13.880
Said Hatch.

34:13.880 --> 34:16.920
Sir Daniel wants to kill you, but not Joanna.

34:17.640 --> 34:19.400
I want to help you both escape.

34:20.280 --> 34:21.640
Here is the key to the door.

34:21.880 --> 34:26.840
He took an old key from his pocket, and opened the big door.

34:26.840 --> 34:30.440
Now you can escape across the church to the tower.

34:30.440 --> 34:33.240
I'll tell Sir Daniel I couldn't find you.

34:33.240 --> 34:34.440
Good luck.

34:38.840 --> 34:40.840
Listening activity.

34:42.840 --> 34:45.240
My parents died when I was only 12.

34:45.240 --> 34:46.840
How did they die?

34:46.840 --> 34:50.040
There was a terrible fire at my house.

34:50.040 --> 34:53.480
A terrible fire at my home, Crombie Hall.

34:53.480 --> 34:55.000
Oh, how awful.

34:55.720 --> 34:56.440
What happened?

34:57.160 --> 34:59.000
Only I escaped the fire.

34:59.720 --> 35:04.360
After that, Lord Foxham, a good friend of my father, looked after me.

35:05.240 --> 35:10.280
Then one day Sir Daniel invited us to a party at Mothouse Castle.

35:11.320 --> 35:15.320
We went, and Sir Daniel asked me to stay for a few weeks.

35:16.200 --> 35:19.320
I stayed, but then he didn't let me leave.

35:20.040 --> 35:21.400
How did you get away from him?

35:22.280 --> 35:24.440
Lord Foxham came with his soldiers.

35:25.160 --> 35:27.240
He ordered Sir Richard to let me go.

35:28.360 --> 35:32.760
Some years passed, Lord Foxham wanted me to marry Lord Hamley.

35:33.480 --> 35:33.960
Hamley?

35:34.760 --> 35:35.400
But why?

35:36.120 --> 35:38.200
He was a good friend of Lord Foxham.

35:38.920 --> 35:41.320
Lord Foxham thought I would be happy with him.

35:42.280 --> 35:45.320
Hamley was a good man, but very old.

35:45.960 --> 35:47.480
I didn't want to marry him.

35:48.520 --> 35:49.640
Then what happened?

35:50.200 --> 35:54.760
Well, then Sir Daniel came one day with three of his soldiers.

35:55.400 --> 35:59.720
I was in the garden at Lord Foxham's house when they came and kidnapped me.

36:03.960 --> 36:07.080
Chapter 5, Ellis Duckworth.

36:09.640 --> 36:14.040
Richard and Joanna ran across the church to the castle tower.

36:15.400 --> 36:18.200
Richard tied the rope around a big stone.

36:19.080 --> 36:21.720
He looked back and saw no one.

36:23.160 --> 36:27.320
We must climb down the tower to the moat and swim to the other side.

36:27.320 --> 36:30.840
He said, then we can run to the forest and we'll be free.

36:31.560 --> 36:32.280
Very well.

36:32.760 --> 36:34.360
Said Joanna bravely.

36:35.000 --> 36:37.080
I'll go first and you can follow me.

36:37.080 --> 36:40.120
Said Richard, can you climb down a rope Joanna?

36:40.600 --> 36:41.160
I'll try.

36:41.720 --> 36:42.200
She said.

36:43.800 --> 36:46.280
Richard started climbing down the rope.

36:47.080 --> 36:50.920
One of Sir Daniel's men on the other tower saw him.

36:51.480 --> 36:53.400
Shelton's trying to escape.

36:54.120 --> 36:54.840
He shouted.

36:55.720 --> 36:58.520
He shot Richard in the arm with an arrow.

37:00.120 --> 37:04.200
Richard fell into the moat and tried to swim to the other side.

37:05.320 --> 37:08.120
Arrows were flying from the tower into the moat.

37:09.400 --> 37:13.960
When Joanna saw Richard falling into the moat, she screamed.

37:14.760 --> 37:19.000
One of Sir Daniel's men heard her and took her by the arm.

37:20.200 --> 37:22.440
She was Sir Daniel's prisoner again.

37:24.840 --> 37:28.280
Richard got out of the water and ran into the forest.

37:29.320 --> 37:34.120
From there, he could see Moat House Castle, but he could not see Joanna.

37:35.400 --> 37:39.000
One of Sir Daniel's men probably caught her, he thought.

37:39.000 --> 37:42.840
But Sir Daniel won't hurt her because he wants to plan her marriage.

37:43.640 --> 37:45.640
I'll come back and rescue her soon.

37:46.920 --> 37:49.640
His arm hurt and he could not walk.

37:50.520 --> 37:52.520
He fell to the ground on the leaves.

37:54.280 --> 37:57.960
Ellis Duckworth and another man found Richard the next morning.

37:59.000 --> 38:02.920
He was very ill, so they took him to an inn and put him to bed.

38:04.600 --> 38:07.080
When Richard woke up, he said.

38:07.080 --> 38:10.680
Oh, my arm and head hurt a lot.

38:11.640 --> 38:14.920
Ellis Duckworth took his hand and smiled.

38:14.920 --> 38:21.320
My dear boy, I'm Ellis Duckworth and I was your father's best friend.

38:22.120 --> 38:24.040
He was like a brother to me.

38:25.160 --> 38:26.920
He looked at the other man and said,

38:27.560 --> 38:30.360
He's lawless, one of my best men.

38:31.720 --> 38:34.280
Now, Richard, please sleep.

38:35.080 --> 38:38.920
When you're better, you'll tell me your story and we'll help you.

38:39.000 --> 38:46.600
The next day, Richard was feeling better and he told Ellis Duckworth his long story.

38:46.600 --> 38:50.440
I'm happy you're here with us, said Ellis.

38:50.440 --> 38:56.280
We're the band of the Black Arrow and we want to punish bad people.

38:56.280 --> 38:59.720
I know you're brave and loyal, Richard.

38:59.720 --> 39:06.120
Together, we'll fight and destroy Sir Daniel and we'll rescue Joanna too.

39:06.200 --> 39:09.720
But first, we must find out where she is.

39:10.840 --> 39:17.320
A few days later, a mysterious messenger took this letter to Mothouse Castle.

39:18.520 --> 39:23.720
To Sir Daniel Brackley, you are a bad man.

39:23.720 --> 39:26.760
You are greedy and dishonest.

39:26.760 --> 39:30.280
Now I know you killed my father.

39:30.280 --> 39:33.800
One day, I will kill you.

39:33.960 --> 39:37.720
Leave Joanna, sadly alone.

39:38.760 --> 39:40.360
I want to marry her soon.

39:41.720 --> 39:42.680
Richard Shelton.

39:45.080 --> 39:47.400
Sir Daniel read the letter and thought,

39:48.120 --> 39:50.360
That boy is dangerous.

39:51.480 --> 39:52.520
I must find him.

39:54.200 --> 39:57.240
Many months passed and it was already winter.

39:58.360 --> 40:03.480
The House of Lancaster won a lot of battles and became strong and important.

40:04.360 --> 40:06.280
York was very weak now.

40:08.200 --> 40:12.680
The town of Shorby on the tilt was full of Lancaster nobles.

40:13.720 --> 40:20.280
Sir Daniel with 60 men, his friend Lord Shorby with 200 men and many others.

40:21.960 --> 40:29.080
One cold winter night in January, three men of the band of the Black Arrow sat in a dark inn.

40:30.040 --> 40:31.640
I don't like this place.

40:32.360 --> 40:33.480
Said one man.

40:33.480 --> 40:35.160
There are too many enemies here.

40:36.920 --> 40:40.600
We're here to help Master Shelton, said Lawless.

40:42.280 --> 40:45.000
Suddenly, a young man came into the inn.

40:45.800 --> 40:48.280
Master Shelton, said Lawless.

40:48.280 --> 40:51.400
Sir Daniel left the inn a few minutes ago with six men.

40:53.640 --> 40:55.720
Let's follow him, said Richard.

40:56.920 --> 40:58.280
It was dark outside.

40:59.080 --> 41:02.840
But they could see Sir Daniel and his men walking towards the sea.

41:04.760 --> 41:08.280
Near the sea, they saw an old lord with some men.

41:09.240 --> 41:10.520
He was short and fat.

41:11.480 --> 41:15.160
He met Sir Daniel in front of a stone house with a wall around it.

41:16.360 --> 41:21.240
Richard and his men hid behind some trees and watched the two men.

41:22.280 --> 41:23.960
But they could not hear them speak.

41:24.920 --> 41:28.920
It's old Lord Shorby, thought Richard angrily.

41:28.920 --> 41:30.600
He's another greedy man.

41:32.200 --> 41:36.120
Tell me, Sir Daniel, how is the young girl?

41:37.240 --> 41:38.360
Ask the old lord.

41:39.480 --> 41:41.480
Is she very beautiful?

41:42.440 --> 41:45.400
Lord Shorby, said Sir Daniel.

41:45.480 --> 41:50.840
Joanna Cidley's young, beautiful and very rich.

41:51.880 --> 41:53.800
She'll be an excellent wife.

41:54.680 --> 41:58.600
The Cidley family was very rich and very important.

41:59.480 --> 42:01.240
She'll bring you a lot of money.

42:02.200 --> 42:05.320
And I'll pay you a lot of money, Sir Daniel.

42:05.880 --> 42:09.880
But I want to see her now, said Lord Shorby.

42:11.160 --> 42:15.080
Sir Daniel and Lord Shorby went into the stone house,

42:15.080 --> 42:16.280
followed by their men.

42:17.240 --> 42:21.800
When they came out, Lord Shorby was smiling and went home.

42:22.920 --> 42:25.800
Sir Daniel and his men went back to the inn.

42:27.240 --> 42:31.160
Now we know Joanna is Sir Daniel's prisoner, said Richard,

42:31.160 --> 42:35.720
and Lord Shorby wants to marry her, that greedy old man.

42:36.440 --> 42:38.120
We must stop this marriage.

42:38.680 --> 42:40.680
I want to look inside of the house.

42:41.240 --> 42:42.840
Lawless, come with me, please.

42:43.400 --> 42:44.760
The others can wait here.

42:46.200 --> 42:49.160
Richard climbed to the top of the stone wall.

42:50.280 --> 42:54.200
From there, he could see the kitchen window and Joanna.

42:55.320 --> 42:59.000
She was sitting at a table with Bennett Hatch's wife,

42:59.000 --> 43:02.120
and three of Sir Daniel's men stood behind her.

43:03.640 --> 43:06.440
She's very beautiful, thought Richard.

43:07.400 --> 43:09.400
He was happy to see her,

43:09.400 --> 43:12.280
but he was angry with Sir Daniel and Lord Shorby.

43:13.320 --> 43:16.600
He climbed down the wall and said to his men,

43:16.600 --> 43:19.240
I saw Joanna, she's inside.

43:19.800 --> 43:21.080
We must rescue her.

43:21.800 --> 43:23.400
Let's think of a good plan.

43:27.640 --> 43:31.080
Chapter 6 The Two Friars

43:31.720 --> 43:39.800
Richard and the men of the Black Arrow decided to attack Sir Daniel's house near the sea

43:40.360 --> 43:41.800
and rescue Joanna.

43:43.720 --> 43:49.080
That night, Richard and his 20 men climbed over the wall of the house,

43:50.040 --> 43:54.120
but Sir Daniel's men attacked them before they could get into the house.

43:55.080 --> 43:59.320
Sir Daniel had 60 men, and Richard had only 20.

44:00.200 --> 44:06.120
His men fought bravely, but they could not get into the house and rescue Joanna.

44:07.480 --> 44:10.600
Many men were hurt, and some were killed.

44:11.800 --> 44:13.560
They went back to the forest.

44:15.640 --> 44:18.760
When Sir Daniel heard about the attack, he said,

44:19.480 --> 44:22.760
Shelton wants to rescue Joanna and marry her.

44:23.400 --> 44:26.120
We must take her to my castle in Shorby.

44:26.840 --> 44:30.920
She'll be safe there, and she'll marry Lord Shorby in a few days.

44:32.520 --> 44:36.280
The next morning, Richard and Lola sat by the fire.

44:37.640 --> 44:43.640
If we don't rescue Joanna, she'll have to marry that old Lord, said Richard sadly.

44:44.280 --> 44:45.160
What can we do?

44:46.840 --> 44:48.840
Lola looked at him and said,

44:49.800 --> 44:51.080
Perhaps I can help you.

44:52.120 --> 44:52.680
Follow me.

44:54.040 --> 44:54.840
Where are we going?

44:55.400 --> 44:59.400
Asked Richard to a secret place, said Lola's.

45:01.000 --> 45:04.600
They walked in the snow to a small den under a big tree.

45:05.880 --> 45:10.040
Inside the den, there was a table and a wooden box.

45:11.320 --> 45:14.120
This is my secret den, said Lola's.

45:14.920 --> 45:18.360
Your secret den, said Richard, surprised.

45:18.360 --> 45:19.400
It's very small.

45:20.200 --> 45:25.400
Lola's opened the wooden box and took out a friar's robe.

45:26.200 --> 45:27.640
It was old and brown.

45:28.760 --> 45:30.280
Then he took out another one.

45:31.560 --> 45:32.280
What are these?

45:33.000 --> 45:33.720
Asked Richard.

45:34.280 --> 45:35.880
They're two friar's robes.

45:36.760 --> 45:40.200
Let's put them on, and everyone will think we're friars.

45:41.560 --> 45:42.120
But why?

45:42.840 --> 45:44.600
Asked Richard, confused.

45:45.320 --> 45:49.720
With these robes, no one will recognize us, said Lola's.

45:49.720 --> 45:52.920
We can easily get into Sir Daniel's castle in Shorby.

45:53.640 --> 45:56.120
Remember, no one stops a friar.

45:57.640 --> 45:59.400
Sir Daniel's castle in Shorby.

46:00.200 --> 46:00.840
But why?

46:01.400 --> 46:02.120
Asked Richard.

46:03.240 --> 46:04.440
Master Shelton.

46:05.000 --> 46:05.960
Cried Lola's.

46:05.960 --> 46:10.760
Joanna is now in his castle, and she'll soon marry old Lord Shorby.

46:11.800 --> 46:13.000
Now do you understand?

46:13.960 --> 46:15.800
Richard was very surprised.

46:16.600 --> 46:17.560
How do you know this?

46:18.200 --> 46:18.760
He asked.

46:19.400 --> 46:23.720
Young man, I'm lawless, and I'm much older than you.

46:24.440 --> 46:26.520
I know a lot of things you don't know.

46:28.040 --> 46:29.720
But how can we stop this marriage?

46:30.280 --> 46:31.080
Asked Richard.

46:32.120 --> 46:34.520
We'll think of a plan, said Lola's.

46:35.080 --> 46:37.400
Now, put on the friar's robe.

46:38.680 --> 46:41.320
Richard put on the robe and asked.

46:42.280 --> 46:43.080
How do I look?

46:44.920 --> 46:45.640
Not bad.

46:46.520 --> 46:50.280
But I must do something to your face now, answered Lola's.

46:51.480 --> 46:54.120
He took some dark pencils from the box,

46:54.680 --> 46:58.360
and drew a moustache and a small beard on Richard's young face.

47:00.040 --> 47:01.880
Perfect, he said.

47:01.880 --> 47:03.320
Now you look like a friar.

47:04.120 --> 47:08.200
Remember to keep your hood on, and no one will recognize you.

47:08.840 --> 47:13.160
Lola's put on the other robe, and they left the den.

47:14.360 --> 47:17.640
When they got to Shorby, they went to the castle.

47:18.600 --> 47:21.080
There were a lot of people at the castle,

47:21.080 --> 47:23.400
rich gentlemen with their ladies,

47:23.400 --> 47:27.800
soldiers, merchants, musicians, and acrobats.

47:29.000 --> 47:32.120
The two friars went to a soldier and said,

47:32.120 --> 47:34.680
we're here to visit Joanna, saidly.

47:34.680 --> 47:36.600
We're here to visit Joanna, saidly.

47:37.720 --> 47:41.240
A room is on the second floor, said the soldier.

47:42.600 --> 47:47.320
The two friars went to the second floor and found Joanna's room.

47:48.120 --> 47:50.600
I'll wait outside, said Lola's.

47:52.280 --> 47:56.040
Richard entered Joanna's room and took off his hood.

47:57.240 --> 47:57.800
Joanna?

47:58.600 --> 48:00.040
He said softly.

48:00.040 --> 48:01.800
It's me, Richard.

48:02.680 --> 48:05.320
She ran to him, and they hugged.

48:05.880 --> 48:06.920
Oh, Richard!

48:06.920 --> 48:08.200
Joanna said,

48:08.200 --> 48:10.120
I'm happy to see you.

48:10.680 --> 48:12.120
What are you doing here?

48:12.680 --> 48:15.960
I'm here with a friend, to rescue you, said Richard.

48:15.960 --> 48:16.920
But how?

48:16.920 --> 48:18.360
Joanna asked.

48:18.760 --> 48:23.560
I'm Sir Daniel's prisoner, and I have to marry Lord Shorby tomorrow morning.

48:24.120 --> 48:27.800
I'm so unhappy, because I don't want to marry him.

48:28.360 --> 48:30.840
You won't marry that horrible old man,

48:31.160 --> 48:31.880
said Richard.

48:31.880 --> 48:34.520
I promised Joanna, I want to marry you.

48:35.720 --> 48:38.840
He put on his hood and left the room quietly.

48:39.960 --> 48:42.840
He and Lola's went to the church to think of a plan.

48:43.960 --> 48:47.080
But Richard met Sir Oliver in the church.

48:48.920 --> 48:52.200
Richard Shelton, he said, surprised.

48:53.160 --> 48:54.680
Sir Daniel is looking for you.

48:55.400 --> 48:56.840
You're in great danger.

48:57.400 --> 49:00.600
I'm here to stop Joanna's marriage, said Richard.

49:00.840 --> 49:02.680
I'm not afraid of Sir Daniel.

49:03.400 --> 49:06.680
You can't stop this marriage, said the priest,

49:07.400 --> 49:09.320
because Sir Daniel will kill you.

49:10.200 --> 49:13.560
You must stay in this church until tomorrow morning,

49:13.560 --> 49:14.440
and then leave.

49:15.160 --> 49:18.680
If you try to escape, I'll call the soldiers.

49:21.000 --> 49:23.560
Richard and Lola's could not move.

49:25.160 --> 49:29.240
At nine o'clock the next morning, there were a lot of people in the church.

49:30.200 --> 49:32.200
Richard and Lola's were there too.

49:33.720 --> 49:37.320
Joanna was wearing a beautiful white dress,

49:37.320 --> 49:39.000
and had flowers in her hair.

49:40.040 --> 49:42.040
But she was pale and sad.

49:43.400 --> 49:47.080
Old Lord Shorby was wearing his best clothes.

49:48.920 --> 49:52.360
Joanna and Lord Shorby stood in front of the priest.

49:53.480 --> 49:57.640
Ellis Duckworth and his men were hiding on the stairs of the church tower.

49:58.360 --> 50:05.400
Suddenly, a black arrow flew across the church and killed Lord Shorby.

50:07.160 --> 50:09.880
Joanna and the people in the church screamed.

50:10.840 --> 50:14.360
Sir Daniel and his men took Joanna away immediately.

50:15.560 --> 50:19.240
Richard and Lola's were angry, but they could do nothing.

50:20.360 --> 50:23.160
They watched Joanna leave with Sir Daniel.

50:23.960 --> 50:28.280
Chapter 7

50:29.720 --> 50:31.320
The Victory of York

50:33.880 --> 50:37.000
Richard and Lola's returned to the forest.

50:38.360 --> 50:42.600
That night, Ellis Duckworth's men sat around the fire.

50:44.200 --> 50:46.840
There's going to be an important battle tomorrow

50:46.840 --> 50:51.400
between the houses of Lancaster and York, said Duckworth to his men.

50:51.400 --> 50:53.640
We're going to attack Shorby Castle.

50:54.360 --> 50:56.120
This time, York will win.

50:58.120 --> 50:58.840
Cried the men.

50:59.640 --> 51:02.440
And we're going to find my enemy, Sir Daniel.

51:03.240 --> 51:07.400
Remember, there's a black arrow waiting for him and his good friends,

51:07.400 --> 51:09.400
Bennett Hatch, and Sir Oliver Oates.

51:10.360 --> 51:11.720
We'll find them!

51:12.360 --> 51:13.000
Cried the men.

51:14.040 --> 51:15.880
Richard said Duckworth.

51:15.880 --> 51:19.720
Go and meet the Duke of Gloucester at some bridges cross tomorrow morning.

51:20.440 --> 51:22.280
Take him this important message.

51:23.800 --> 51:26.520
Dear Richard, Duke of Gloucester,

51:27.400 --> 51:32.680
my twenty men will meet your soldiers outside Shorby Castle before the battle.

51:33.560 --> 51:35.800
We will fight together and win.

51:36.920 --> 51:38.040
Ellis Duckworth.

51:39.080 --> 51:43.720
Very early the next morning, Richard rode to St. Bridget's Cross.

51:45.080 --> 51:49.080
It was a cold morning and there was a lot of snow on the road.

51:50.280 --> 51:55.640
When he got there, he saw a young knight dressed in armor on a big black horse.

51:56.760 --> 52:00.280
The white rose of the house of York was on his shield.

52:01.240 --> 52:04.520
He was alone and he was fighting eight soldiers.

52:05.720 --> 52:09.160
He was a good fighter and killed three soldiers.

52:09.800 --> 52:12.040
I can help you, sir, Cried Richard.

52:12.760 --> 52:17.000
He and the knight fought together and the fight was soon over.

52:17.880 --> 52:19.880
The young knight was surprised.

52:20.520 --> 52:22.520
He turned to Richard and said,

52:22.520 --> 52:24.280
Thank you for your help.

52:24.280 --> 52:27.240
You're a good fighter and you saved my life.

52:27.880 --> 52:28.760
Who are you?

52:28.760 --> 52:32.360
I'm Richard Shelton and I'm looking for the Duke of Gloucester.

52:32.360 --> 52:34.360
Well, you found him.

52:34.360 --> 52:35.560
Said the knight.

52:35.560 --> 52:38.120
I'm Richard, Duke of Gloucester.

52:39.080 --> 52:41.160
Here's a message from Ellis Duckworth.

52:41.160 --> 52:43.800
Said Richard, giving him the letter.

52:44.440 --> 52:47.400
The Duke read the letter and said,

52:47.400 --> 52:51.080
Good, I need more brave men for this battle.

52:51.080 --> 52:55.480
Duckworth is a loyal friend and together we'll win.

52:55.480 --> 52:59.000
Soon, the Duke soldiers arrived.

52:59.000 --> 53:02.920
They were carrying flags with the white rose of York.

53:02.920 --> 53:05.080
We're ready, he cried.

53:05.080 --> 53:07.560
Let's attack Shobikasul!

53:09.400 --> 53:12.840
Many of the soldiers at Shobikasul are here.

53:12.840 --> 53:16.600
The soldiers at Shobikasul were still sleeping when the Duke attacked.

53:17.800 --> 53:22.280
Hundreds of soldiers fought in a long battle and many were killed.

53:23.640 --> 53:29.560
At the end of the battle, there was a fire and Shobikasul was almost destroyed.

53:30.840 --> 53:38.520
The House of York won the battle and Sir Daniel escaped with Joanna, Bennett Hatch and two men.

53:38.520 --> 53:43.560
The Duke of Gloucester was pleased with the victory.

53:44.520 --> 53:50.600
He went to Richard and said, You're a brave young man and you fought well.

53:51.720 --> 53:54.840
Kneel down, Richard, I want to knight you.

53:56.440 --> 54:01.320
Richard knelt down in front of the Duke and became Sir Richard.

54:02.200 --> 54:04.280
This was a great honor for him.

54:04.600 --> 54:10.680
The next day Sir Richard left Shobikasul and started looking for Joanna.

54:10.680 --> 54:13.800
He knew she was with Sir Daniel.

54:13.800 --> 54:20.280
He traveled all day and in the evening he saw a small fire on a hill.

54:20.280 --> 54:24.600
Perhaps that's Sir Daniel's fire, he thought.

54:24.600 --> 54:29.560
He moved silently through the trees and got closer.

54:29.560 --> 54:36.440
He saw Sir Daniel, Bennett Hatch and a young boy sitting near the fire.

54:37.640 --> 54:39.160
They were eating and talking.

54:40.040 --> 54:46.200
Joanna is dressed as John Matcham again, thought Richard, Sir Daniel is very clever.

54:48.120 --> 54:51.560
Richard hid behind a big tree and watched them.

54:52.520 --> 54:55.240
It was obvious that Joanna was very sad.

54:56.040 --> 55:01.880
He waited until they were finally asleep and then he quietly went up to Joanna.

55:03.320 --> 55:07.480
Joanna, he whispered in her ear, Wake up!

55:08.360 --> 55:10.600
She woke up and smiled.

55:11.320 --> 55:14.840
We must be very quiet, whispered Sir Richard.

55:14.840 --> 55:18.040
Get up slowly and follow me.

55:19.480 --> 55:22.760
They moved away very quietly through the trees.

55:23.720 --> 55:27.400
They got on Sir Richard's horse and went into the forest.

55:28.440 --> 55:33.000
That night they slept at Ellis Duckworth's camp near Holywood.

55:34.520 --> 55:41.080
When Joanna woke up, she said, This is like a dream Richard, we're together again.

55:41.720 --> 55:46.360
Yes, and tomorrow we can get married, Sir Richard said excitedly.

55:46.360 --> 55:50.040
I'm going to talk to the kind friar of Holywood Abbey this morning.

55:50.840 --> 55:53.720
I'm very happy, Richard, said Joanna.

55:56.520 --> 56:00.520
Sir Richard woke up very early on the day of his marriage.

56:01.480 --> 56:03.880
He was the happiest man in the world.

56:05.720 --> 56:09.560
He put on his best clothes and took a short walk in the forest.

56:10.760 --> 56:13.560
Soon he saw a friar walking towards him.

56:14.840 --> 56:17.960
As the friar came closer, he recognized him.

56:18.920 --> 56:20.200
It was Sir Daniel.

56:21.160 --> 56:24.680
He put his hand on his sword because he was ready to fight.

56:25.240 --> 56:27.160
I'm not here to fight you.

56:27.800 --> 56:29.320
Said Sir Daniel sadly.

56:29.960 --> 56:36.040
My men and I fought bravely, but we lost the battle against the House of York.

56:37.000 --> 56:41.720
It was a long, terrible battle, and now I have nothing.

56:42.680 --> 56:46.920
I lost my castle, my men, my money.

56:47.720 --> 56:48.520
My jewels.

56:49.720 --> 56:50.680
I lost everything.

56:51.960 --> 56:56.280
Now I must escape to France, where I still have some friends.

56:57.240 --> 56:58.920
I hope they can help me.

57:00.040 --> 57:06.120
Go to France, Sir Daniel, and don't come back, said Sir Richard angrily.

57:07.720 --> 57:11.400
Sir Daniel turned around and continued walking in the forest.

57:12.360 --> 57:21.160
But after a minute, a black arrow flew through the morning air and hit him in the heart.

57:22.600 --> 57:26.520
He fell to the ground, and Sir Richard ran to his side.

57:28.760 --> 57:29.240
Richard?

57:29.880 --> 57:31.080
He said quietly.

57:32.120 --> 57:35.000
Is the arrow black?

57:36.920 --> 57:38.920
Yes, it's black.

57:39.800 --> 57:40.520
Said Richard.

57:42.120 --> 57:45.960
Sir Daniel looked at him for the last time and died.

57:47.880 --> 57:48.680
I killed him.

57:49.400 --> 57:50.760
Said a voice in the forest.

57:51.880 --> 57:53.800
It was Ellis Duckworth.

57:53.800 --> 57:56.280
And yesterday I killed Bennett Hatch.

57:57.640 --> 58:00.520
He walked out of the forest and stood by Richard.

58:01.720 --> 58:05.560
You killed all of your enemies except one, said Richard.

58:06.280 --> 58:09.480
Yes, Sir Oliver is still alive.

58:09.480 --> 58:10.600
Said Duckworth.

58:10.600 --> 58:12.840
Don't kill him, Ellis, said Richard.

58:13.640 --> 58:14.760
Let's live in peace.

58:16.680 --> 58:18.760
Duckworth thought for a moment.

58:19.960 --> 58:22.360
He looked at the body of Sir Daniel and said,

58:23.000 --> 58:24.200
You're right, Richard.

58:25.000 --> 58:26.360
I want to live in peace.

58:27.320 --> 58:30.440
I don't want to fight or kill anymore.

58:31.320 --> 58:35.720
The band of the black arrow doesn't exist anymore.

58:37.960 --> 58:44.600
At nine o'clock that morning, Richard and Joanna finally got married at Hollywood Abbey.

58:45.640 --> 58:49.240
It was a beautiful wedding, and everyone was happy.

58:50.360 --> 58:57.640
Richard, Joanna, Ellis Duckworth, the men of the black arrow, and the Duke of Gloucester and his

58:57.640 --> 59:00.280
soldiers celebrated with a dinner.

59:01.800 --> 59:09.640
Richard and Joanna lived a happy, peaceful life in the forest, far from wars and battles.

59:13.400 --> 59:15.720
Knights and the Night Hood today.

59:17.480 --> 59:24.280
Today the title Knight refers to people who receive this honor from the king or queen.

59:25.080 --> 59:28.920
It is a thank you for good services to the country.

59:29.960 --> 59:35.640
But in the Middle Ages, a knight was a soldier who fought for the king and the country.

59:37.960 --> 59:42.680
Knights in the Middle Ages almost always came from noble families.

59:43.640 --> 59:49.880
They had a high position in society and worked for lords or directly for the king.

59:50.680 --> 59:57.000
When they went into battle, they wore heavy armor and rode strong horses.

59:58.040 --> 01:00:04.680
They carried a special shield with their family symbol called a coat of arms.

01:00:06.280 --> 01:00:13.000
When they weren't fighting in battles, knights often practiced their skills by going to tournaments.

01:00:13.640 --> 01:00:21.240
These were big competitions, and there were several different sports, including jousting.

01:00:22.920 --> 01:00:26.600
Boys learned how to become a knight from the age of seven.

01:00:27.640 --> 01:00:30.440
These young boys were called pages.

01:00:31.640 --> 01:00:36.840
They learned about horses and armor and how to fight with a wooden sword.

01:00:37.960 --> 01:00:41.800
When they were around twelve, they became squires.

01:00:43.000 --> 01:00:46.600
A squire learned how to fight from a real knight.

01:00:47.480 --> 01:00:54.360
He also helped the knight do many things, including putting on his armor before going into battle.

01:00:56.040 --> 01:01:01.720
Today's knights do not need to fight, and they do not have a specific job to do.

01:01:02.920 --> 01:01:06.120
The special honor is called a knight hood.

01:01:07.160 --> 01:01:11.080
In Great Britain, these awards are given twice a year.

01:01:11.720 --> 01:01:18.440
If you are knighted by the queen, you are then invited to a special ceremony at Buckingham Palace.

01:01:19.480 --> 01:01:25.720
Here, you kneel in front of the queen, and she touches your shoulders with a sword.

01:01:27.080 --> 01:01:36.680
A British man can then use Sir before his name, and a British woman can use Dame before hers.

01:01:37.560 --> 01:01:43.560
Sometimes, the queen awards an honorary knight hood to non-British citizens.

01:01:44.600 --> 01:01:49.160
These people are knighted, but they cannot officially use the title.

01:01:50.200 --> 01:01:54.520
Recent examples are Bob Gildorf and Bill Gates.

01:01:55.880 --> 01:02:02.600
Often, non-famous people are given a knight hood to say thank you for their charity work.

01:02:06.680 --> 01:02:16.680
